All items fluid and left-aligned

Shorten the page to test how long menus work when they are taller than the window.

Note: The rest of this page is filled with examples of the various supported configurations. Each configuration is shown twice, once with Empire 2 styles and once with another set of styles, to show how multiple menu styles can co-exist.

Example 2

The menu has both left-aligned & right-aligned items. In this case, all items must be fixed-width to introduce a gap between the two sides, otherwise the result is structurally identical to the first and fourth examples.

Example 3

Same as above, but with pixel widths instead of percentages. Any unused space will appear pink.

This is the only scenario where the menu may not fill its container entirely.
